<subSubSection id="C368652E93538E0EF2AAFA9EFC63FA81" pageId="10" pageNumber="494" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A593538E0EF2AAFA9EFC63FA81" blockId="10.[151,1437,1292,1535]" pageId="10" pageNumber="494">
<materialsCitation id="3B1A3CF893538E0EF2AAFA9EFC7FFA81" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798147331" collectorName="J. Serrano" pageId="10" pageNumber="494" specimenCount="2" typeStatus="lectotype">
The specimen here designated as 
<typeStatus id="54C9880793538E0EF033FA9EFDA4FAED" box="[526,629,1292,1318]" pageId="10" pageNumber="494">lectotype</typeStatus>
is a male bearing a white label “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693538E0EF1DFFA9EFBE9FAED" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[994,1080,1292,1318]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Stenolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="494" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793538E0EF1DFFA9EFBE9FAED" box="[994,1080,1292,1318]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="494">elegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
m. in Dalmatia” and a red label “ 
<typeStatus id="54C9880793538E0EF29CFAA2FEC5FA81" box="[161,276,1328,1354]" pageId="10" pageNumber="494">Lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693538E0EF304FAA2FD6AFA81" authority="Dejean, 1829" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[313,699,1328,1354]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Stenolophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="494" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793538E0EF304FAA2FDCEFA81" box="[313,543,1328,1354]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="494">Stenolophus elegans</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493538E0EF018FAA2FD6AFA81" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[549,699,1328,1354]" pageId="10" pageNumber="494" refId="ref10732" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1829) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome quatrieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, vii + 520 pp." type="book" year="1829">Dejean, 1829</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
desig. by 
<collectorName id="2687537393538E0EF113FAA3FC75FA81" box="[814,932,1328,1355]" pageId="10" pageNumber="494">J. Serrano</collectorName>
”
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C368652E93538E0EF2FAFAC6FD5FFA35" pageId="10" pageNumber="494" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A593538E0EF2FAFAC6FBB5FA7D" blockId="10.[151,1437,1292,1535]" pageId="10" pageNumber="494">
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493538E0EF2FAFAC6FEB6FAA5" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[199,359,1364,1390]" pageId="10" pageNumber="494" refId="ref10732" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1829) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome quatrieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, vii + 520 pp." type="book" year="1829">Dejean (1829)</bibRefCitation>
could examine a number of beetles to describe the species. I have selected a male from Dalmatia that is well conserved and clearly shows the characters of main taxonomic interest: large body size, male protarsomeres notably dilated, antennomeres 1-2 pale, etc. (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493538E0EF0E5FA0EFCA6FA7D" author="Jeannel, R." box="[728,887,1436,1462]" pageId="10" pageNumber="494" pagination="572 - 1173" refId="ref11231" refString="Jeannel, R. (1942) Coleopteres carabiques. Deuxieme partie. Faune de France 40. Librairie de la Faculte des Sciences, Paris, pp. 572 - 1173." type="book chapter" year="1942">Jeannel, 1942</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493538E0EF1BFFA0FFBC0FA7D" author="Wrase, D. W." box="[898,1041,1436,1463]" pageId="10" pageNumber="494" pagination="344 - 386" refId="ref12516" refString="Wrase, D. W. (2004) Harpalina. In: Freude, H., Harde, K. W., Lohse, G. A. &amp; Klausnitzer, B. (Eds.), Die Kafer Mitteleuropas. Bd. 2 Adephaga 1: Carabidae (Laufkafer). Spektrum-Verlag, Heidelberg / Berlin, pp. 344 - 386." type="book chapter" year="2004">Wrase, 2004</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493538E0EF621FA0EFB89FA7D" author="Wrase, D. W." box="[1052,1112,1436,1462]" pageId="10" pageNumber="494" refId="ref12634" refString="Wrase, D. W. (2011) Genus Tschitscherinellus. Arndt, E., Schnitter, P., Sfenthourakis, S. &amp; Wrase, D. W. (Eds.), Ground beetles (Carabidae) of Greece. Pensoft, Sofia, pp. 163." type="book" year="2011">2011</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36A593538E0EF2FAFA52FD5FFA35" blockId="10.[151,1437,1292,1535]" pageId="10" pageNumber="494">
<materialsCitation id="3B1A3CF893538E0EF2FAFA52FD5BFA35" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798147321" county="Central Asia" location="North Africa" municipality="West Siberia" pageId="10" pageNumber="494" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Canarias">
The species has a large distribution area from 
<collectingCounty id="62AC4E2993538E0EF0F7FA52FC85FA11" box="[714,852,1472,1498]" pageId="10" pageNumber="494">Central Asia</collectingCounty>
and 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BA9ACDF93538E0EF1B7FA53FBC6FA11" box="[906,1047,1472,1499]" pageId="10" pageNumber="494">West Siberia</collectingMunicipality>
to almost all Europe, 
<location id="8EAD607E93538E0EF733FA52FA4CFA11" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03DB87B393538E0EF2AAFB51FD5FFA35:8EAD607E93538E0EF733FA52FA4CFA11" box="[1294,1437,1472,1498]" county="Central Asia" municipality="West Siberia" name="North Africa" pageId="10" pageNumber="494" stateProvince="Canarias">North Africa</location>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49B6F84793538E0EF2FAFA76FEBCFA35" box="[199,365,1508,1534]" country="Spain" name="Canarias" pageId="10" pageNumber="494">Canary Islands</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493538E0EF341FA76FD53FA35" author="Jaeger, B. &amp; Kataev, B. M." box="[380,642,1508,1535]" pageId="10" pageNumber="494" pagination="1837" refId="ref10991" refString="Jaeger, B. &amp; Kataev, B. M. (2017) Subtribe Stenolophina Kirby, 1837. In: Lobl, I. &amp; Lobl, D. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Vol. 1. Revised and Updated Edition. Brill, Leiden, pp. 562 - 577." type="book chapter" year="2017">Jaeger &amp; Kataev, 2017</bibRefCitation>
)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
